NAME
	block_input - block input on a connection

SYNOPSIS
	void block_input(int flag)

DESCRIPTION
	Block or unblock input from the user associated with the current
	object, depending on whether the argument is non-zero or zero,
	respectively.

EXAMPLES
	block_input(1);
	write("You are stunned for 10 seconds.\n");
	sleep(10);
	block_input(0);

SEE ALSO
	kfun/connect, kfun/datagram_challenge, kfun/error,
	kfun/send_datagram, kfun/send_message

